<HEADLINE>
HON HAI TOP IN PATENT APPLICATION, APPROVAL
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Feb. 7 (CNA) 02/07/07  18:13:19 (By Lilian Wu)
</P>
<P>
Hon Hai Precision Industry Co. was top in terms of patent
application and approval for the fourth consecutive year in 2006,
the Intellectual Property Office (IPO) said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
IPO officials noted that in terms of patent applications in 2006,
the top three were the same as 2005, with Hon Hai Precision
Industry Co. top with 1,830 applications, followed by the
Industrial Technology Research Institute (ITRI) with 873 and
Inventec with 819.
</P>
<P>
In terms of applications approved, Hon Hai had 898, ITRI had 583
and Inventec had 493.
</P>
<P>
IPO officials said that since 2003, Hon Hai has maintained top
place in terms of patent application and approval, showing the
company's strength and its efforts in research and development.
</P>
<P>
Royal Philips Electronics was top among foreign institutional
organizations in terms of patent applications with 850, followed
by Samsung Electronics with 747 and Sony with 493, while Sony was
top with 401 patent applications granted, followed by Intel with
364 and Epson with 355.
</P>
<P>
Academic institutes have in recent years been more active in
applying for patents, the officials said, adding that 13 academic
institutes each were on the lost of the top 100 companies or
institutes that applied for patents and received approval in
2006, three more than in 2005.
</P>
<P>
The IPO handled 80,989 applications for patents in 2006, up 1,547
from 2005.
</P>
